profile_positions.description:
•	Established Eurasia Business Operations & Finance activities and processes from scratch with direct report to VP & Head of Eurasia in $4B multinational technology company;
•	Conducted budgeting & planning exercise to support yearly forecast for Eurasia ($150m business);
•	Managed Monthly Business Review (MBR) and Quarterly Business Review (QBR);
•	Established and Managed realistic bottom-up revenue estimation technique to monitor delta vs rolling forecast;
•	Tracked Salesforce opportunties and periodic changes in $500m sales funnel to generate view on revenue impacts;
•	Led sales touchpoints to co-ordinate sales activities and provide supports to pre-sales, sales and delivery teams;
•	Led activities to establish financial standards and methodologies which was widely accepted by entire organization;
•	Established dashboard, financial model and forecasting based on USGAAP revenue recognition guidelines;
•	Drove operational excellence to automate processes and reporting.

•	Established value based pricing for SaaS (Software-as-a-Service) in Software and Technology company:
    o	Created benchmark with legacy subscription pricing, perpetual license and market;
    o	Develope d 5 years business case with full P&L view ($70m) and simulation of scenarios;
    o	Designed & created pricing strategy, processes, documentation and conducted internal training;
•	Developed T-Shirt sizing with revenue estimate and cost modelling;
•	Formulated commercial strategy and product structure of SaaS;
•	Conducted win-loss analysis for reasons of winning or losing deals vs competition and recommend optimum offer;
•	Conducted business trend analysis to forecast multiple scenarios of business growth;
•	Designed opportunity pricing model and conducted investment feasibility analysis with full P&L view (for instance, 10 years business case with $150m value in one of the world’s largest banks and 5 years business case with $100 value in American multinational retail giant);
•	Created deal playbook for sales as a readily available tool to design customer offer;
•	Designed tool for customer ROI (return on investment) and NPV (net present value);
•	Developed pricing discount models for volume discount, sales discount and regional discount.

•	Reported directly to Head of Consumer Business as Chief of Staff in $10B international telecommunication company;
•	Led international projects (SWAT team) with cross functional team of professionals to achieve 5% additional revenue;
•	Delivered annual growth 10-20% by reinventing voice & internet products with monetization initiatives;
•	Redefined strategy by setting short, mid, long term strategic priorities & saved $1M cost as consultancy fee;
•	Achieved 1-2% revenue gain through optimum pricing model by applying data simulation for elasticity analysis;
•	Prepared yearly business plans and budgets with full commercial P&L for all 12 operating companies;
•	Reviewed product & pricing offers with approval authority of business cases generating >=5% revenue impact;
•	Designed and owned strategy framework (Playbook) for likely internal and external scenarios with 50+ cross functional blueprints, toolkit, guidance & best practices;
•	Developed overall business review presentation together with operating companies and recommended actions;
•	Developed factor based forecasting & planning using predictive model for elements of revenue / cost impacts;
•	In Wholesale (international calls & roaming), achieved operational excellence by 100% automation in billing, pricing, reporting and invoice auditing.  This reduced billing & pricing disputes by 50%.

•	Led highly engaged team supporting Marketing, Sales and Customer Care under CCO supervision;
•	Collaborated with FP&A to run commercial control function;
•	Developed 3G investment business plan & product strategy; delivered $26Mln/yr revenue within 2 years after launch;
•	Led ‘Customer Lifetime Value’ project in 12 group companies, delivering 5% revenue upside from priority customers;
•	Slashed costs by 20% product portfolio simplification while leading VEON group project ‘Digital Transformation’;
•	Prepared yearly company budget with full P&L items aiming successful YoY growth 5-10% in 2013-2015;
•	Developed strategy and business case for new product for Youth, resulting 10% higher customer gain;
•	Solved revenue leakage 5% by identifying product mapping discrepancy through deep data analysis;
•	Managed pricing and delivered 2% additional revenue by changing prices during peak, off-peak hours;
•	Prepared monthly (MBR), quarterly (QBR) reports and management presentations for senior management;
•	Participated in project to overhaul bottom-up NPS (net promoter score) process & methodology;
•	Leveraged outcomes of market studies (NPS, loyalty, churn tendancy etc) to integrate in forecasting for the first time.

•	Managed customer lifecycle of AmEx credit cards. Led value proposition, innovation, strategic partnerships, and revenue enhancement initiatives;
•	Established pricing principles & guidelines for merchant acquiring business;
•	Launched usage drive campaign for Amex dormant (silent users) and delivered extra $250K in a quarter;
•	Facilitated 10% increase in Amex sale by conducting training for salesforce to update on product proposition;
•	Led Amex platinum credit card launch; managing business case, value proposition, partnerships & GTM;
•	Initiated Amex reactivation program for long inactive users and delivered 20% additional reactivations;
•	Generated extra 5% fee revenue by introducing product upgradation – regular to gold, gold to platinum;
•	Explored new business of 1-3% revenue gain launching auto debit payment for mobile bill, university fee;
•	Managed strategic partnerships with healthcare institutions, airlines, retail business and amusement parks.
